[1] Switzerland
Date: Tue 4 Sep 2012
Source: Federal Veterinary Office of Switzerland (FVO) official website - News [in German, trans. & summ., edited]
http://www.bvet.admin.ch/gesundheit_tiere/01065/04051/index.html


Schmallenberg virus: investigated samples and new evidence
----------------------------------------------------------
The Institute of Virology and Immunoprophylaxis (IVI) has received, up to 2 Sep 2012, submissions from 78 farms in 19 different cantons related to notified abortions or foetal malformations. This included a total of 81 diagnosed animals: 44 cattle, 23 sheep, and 14 goats. So far, 4 malformed calves tested positive for the Schmallenberg virus [SBV].

Acute cases in adult cattle with diarrhea and fever have recently been reported from 113 farms, 106 of which tested positive for SBV. [The figures, as of 19 Aug 2012, were respectively 77 and 72]. The laboratory results have been based either on the detection of the virus or specific antibodies.

